On Tue, 15 Oct 2002, Alamitos Bays wrote:

> Is this unit just extremely sensitive to slight voltage dips? Or is this a
> clue to something ominous lurking in my electrical system?

Seems to be.  check the voltage with a meter and see if it dips.  If so,
look for a bad connection.  If the dip is small, you could fix it by
putting a diode and capacitor in the circuit to prop up the voltage.

